1
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:12,410
Major Ferguson reporting.

2
00:02:14,240 --> 00:02:15,240
Please, sit down.

3
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:18,840
I'm sorry, Major.

4
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:20,000
You may need to

5
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,360
stay here a few more days.

6
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,240
Why?

7
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,400
After the British withdrawal,

8
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,040
the Japanese have blocked

9
00:02:26,040 --> 00:02:27,920
all our air routes to the China theater.

10
00:02:27,920 --> 00:02:30,180
We're planning to establish a new route.

11
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:32,500
But I told them you're stranded here.

12
00:02:33,079 --> 00:02:33,400
Colonel,

13
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:34,560
I must arrive before April 15th

14
00:02:34,560 --> 00:02:35,200
in China.

15
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:36,560
We still have some time,

16
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:37,890
but we shouldn't delay.

17
00:02:38,720 --> 00:02:40,079
Take a look at this map.

18
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,160
The only possible route

19
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,220
requires flying over the Himalayas.

20
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:46,680
Those mountains are up to 5 miles high.

21
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:49,160
Our planes can't fly that high.

22
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:51,200
We have no maps of that area,

23
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:52,600
no radio guidance,

24
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:55,680
and no clear idea of the actual weather conditions there.

25
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,000
Colonel,

26
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:56,600
you're making it sound like

27
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,130
our mission is impossible.

28
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:00,400
Don't give up yet, Major.

29
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,920
Our pilots are establishing

30
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:03,450
a route over the Himalayas.

31
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:05,940
You'll have to stand by until departure.

32
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,040
Seven-seven-zero-three,

33
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:20,400
prepare for takeoff on 250-meter runway.

34
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:23,840
Seven-seven-zero-three ready.

35
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:27,520
Seven-seven-zero-three, take off.

36
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:39,200
Well done, Jimmy.

37
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,400
I'm very pleased with

38
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,520
the performance of your pilots.

39
00:03:41,520 --> 00:03:41,880
Colonel,

40
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,240
since you proposed this crazy idea,

41
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:45,300
we've certainly accomplished a lot.

42
00:03:46,079 --> 00:03:47,160
At first, the boys were convinced

43
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:48,800
they were going to bomb Hitler.

44
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,240
That's fine.

45
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:51,240
We are considering bombing Hitler.

46
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:52,680
Jimmy,

47
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:54,560
Admiral Halsey will soon arrive in

48
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,800
San Francisco.

49
00:03:55,960 --> 00:03:56,400
He wants

50
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:58,400
you to brief him about this mission.

51
00:03:58,600 --> 00:04:01,240
Despite your impressive performance today,

52
00:04:01,240 --> 00:04:03,240
the Navy isn't fully confident

53
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:04,600
that bombers loaded with fuel and bombs

54
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:08,400
can take off from an aircraft carrier.

55
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:10,560
I'd be happy to personally test fly on the carrier

56
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,280
to show the Admiral.

57
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,440
Good. You do that.

58
00:04:13,760 --> 00:04:16,279
That would be the strongest proof.

59
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:18,320
I've heard

60
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,440
that your squadron's B-24s and B-25s

61
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,519
can't all fit

62
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,720
on the Hornet's deck.

63
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,200
That deck can only accommodate B-15s,

64
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,400
sixteen at best.

65
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,440
That's unfortunate.

66
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,800
With only sixteen planes,

67
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:37,000
we can't really do much damage to Tokyo.

68
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,520
Even with all the B-24s,

69
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,320
you couldn't do much damage either.

70
00:04:40,320 --> 00:04:40,780
Listen,

71
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:42,000
the key to this mission is

72
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:43,360
to send a message to the Japanese,

73
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:45,280
not to cause major destruction.

74
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,560
Not everyone can be a hero.

75
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:51,080
Good pilots are needed for other missions too.

76
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:53,840
Those who can't participate in this mission

77
00:04:53,840 --> 00:04:56,600
will be assigned to other operations.

78
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,850
Perhaps bombing Hitler in Europe.

79
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:04,050
Find a chance to tell everyone about this, would you?

80
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:21,360
Boys,

81
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:24,880
as of today,

82
00:05:24,880 --> 00:05:26,200
the first phase of our training

83
00:05:26,200 --> 00:05:27,360
is coming to an end.

84
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:29,280
I appreciate everyone's

85
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:30,760
efforts with the B-25s.

86
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:33,320
There's still a lot of work to be done.

87
00:05:33,320 --> 00:05:34,120
Colonel, do you mean

88
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,880
adding another broomstick?

89
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:36,680
I bet

90
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,880
Hitler is already shaking in his boots.

91
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:42,080
Many of you have been asking me

92
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,740
what exactly this mission is.

93
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:46,040
I can only repeat what I've said before.

94
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:49,520
This mission is extremely dangerous.

95
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,920
You are not to tell anyone

96
00:05:50,920 --> 00:05:53,050
what we're doing or where we're going.

97
00:05:53,159 --> 00:05:54,880
Not even if your mother asks.

98
00:05:55,520 --> 00:05:56,560
That means you.

99
00:05:57,880 --> 00:06:00,640
This is all top secret.

100
00:06:01,440 --> 00:06:02,440
I will tell you

101
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,700
what you need to know when the time comes.

102
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,480
Any questions?

103
00:06:06,600 --> 00:06:07,960
No, sir.

104
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:09,560
Anyone who's hesitant,

105
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:11,400
anyone who's changed their mind,

106
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,530
tell me now and you can still withdraw.

107
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:16,320
Good.

108
00:06:17,480 --> 00:06:20,120
Tomorrow, our squadron's B-24s

109
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:22,640
will all fly to

110
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:24,440
McClellan Field in Sacramento.

111
00:06:24,640 --> 00:06:26,480
After the transfer,

112
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:27,960
our training mission

113
00:06:27,960 --> 00:06:30,400
will focus on extremely short takeoffs.

114
00:06:32,040 --> 00:06:34,520
A new crew of mechanics will be provided there.

115
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,640
Lawson, Cole,

116
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:38,080
I order you two to supervise them

117
00:06:38,159 --> 00:06:39,560
and speed up our progress.

118
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:40,440
Yes, sir.

119
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,400
That's all.

120
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,240
Have a good evening, everyone.

121
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:43,840
All right.

122
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,880
Short takeoff.

123
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:49,720
What would you like to drink today?

124
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,640
Whiskey.

125
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:53,159
Sir.

126
00:06:53,159 --> 00:06:55,690
Are you really going to Europe to bomb Hitler?

127
00:06:56,200 --> 00:06:57,800
Hitler, Yamamoto, Mussolini.

128
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:58,360
Take your pick.

129
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,680
I'll personally fly you there to meet him.

130
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:02,010
You can jump out of the plane and say hello.

131
00:07:05,120 --> 00:07:06,560
This drink's on me.

132
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:17,720
It's dinner time.

133
00:07:17,720 --> 00:07:20,480
Guests may proceed to the dining room.

134
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:23,360
Miss Ye,

135
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,760
it's time for dinner.

136
00:07:31,840 --> 00:07:32,900
Are you getting up?

137
00:07:33,080 --> 00:07:33,800
What?

138
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:35,720
Well,

139
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:37,520
the announcement just now was that

140
00:07:37,520 --> 00:07:39,240
dinner is being served on the ship.

141
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,440
Shall we go together?

142
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:44,040
After all, we're the only two Chinese people on board.

143
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,100
All right then.

144
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,600
Wait for me.

145
00:08:23,920 --> 00:08:26,320
Hello.

146
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,730
What are you talking about?

147
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:51,240
This Fukuda

148
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:53,740
runs a trading company on the island.

149
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,360
From Tanjiawan to Shangbiao Village,

150
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:58,040
to the Air Force base and Navy dock,

151
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,500
he has stores everywhere.

152
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:02,040
Even the cigarettes Commander Fujita smokes

153
00:09:02,040 --> 00:09:03,200
are supplied by him.

154
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,080
He named all his stores

155
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:07,800
New Nagasaki.

156
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:11,000
I believe he wants to someday

157
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,520
turn Sanzao Island into New Nagasaki.

158
00:09:12,520 --> 00:09:14,440
That way he would be the supreme commander,

159
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:17,900
and General Fujita would be just one of his military officers.

160
00:09:18,760 --> 00:09:20,680
I've got some new cigars

161
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,800
from the Shanghai Concession.

162
00:09:21,800 --> 00:09:23,640
Let's go try them.

163
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:24,600
Let's go.

164
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,240
Let me tell you.

165
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:33,400
He

166
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:37,000
is the only one authorized by the island's Special Police Force

167
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:39,040
to run a comfort station.

168
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,520
He hired over twenty immigrants from Okinawa

169
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:43,600
as workers.

170
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:48,800
He sells everything from daily necessities to food.

171
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,200
Basically anything

172
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:52,600
that can be bought with money.

173
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:55,330
It's all related to him.

174
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,560
Miss Ye.

175
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:00,340
If you need anything on the island in the future,

176
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:01,400
you can come to me.

177
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,360
I have some connections here.

178
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,040
Thank you.

179
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:06,920
As for him,

180
00:10:07,760 --> 00:10:09,960
he's backed by the Special Police Unit.

181
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:12,050
But he's just Oshima Hiroshi's

182
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:14,640
lapdog.

183
00:10:18,800 --> 00:10:21,240
What brings you to the island this time?

184
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,560
I'm going home.

185
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:25,200
Home?

186
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:27,370
My home is on Sanzao Island.

187
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:30,840
My father is Ye Degong.

188
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:35,520
So you're Ye Degong's daughter.

189
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,840
You know my father?

190
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:37,480
Of course.

191
00:10:38,400 --> 00:10:39,360
How is he?

192
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:40,840
He's fine.

193
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:41,560
He's doing well.

194
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,960
His health is excellent.

195
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:44,130
That's good.

196
00:10:44,240 --> 00:10:45,800
I've heard that Ye Degong's daughter

197
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,840
was studying abroad.

198
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:47,960
That's you?

199
00:10:48,560 --> 00:10:49,480
Commander Fujita

200
00:10:49,480 --> 00:10:51,080
used to be in America

201
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,640
as an assistant military attachÃ©.

202
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,840
Your father was a diplomat.

203
00:10:54,840 --> 00:10:56,040
That's why Commander Fujita

204
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,970
enjoys chatting with your father.

205
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:01,920
But perhaps because the military

206
00:11:01,920 --> 00:11:04,320
took over your family's mansion,

207
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,280
your father

208
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:07,210
has never been very enthusiastic.

209
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,480
What's your business?

210
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:03,680
I'm from the Maintenance Association.

211
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:06,520
Who sent you here?

212
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,440
Captain Inoue sent me.

213
00:12:10,200 --> 00:12:11,000
Go on up.

214
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:12,200
Okay.

215
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:33,080
Chairman Tang.

216
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:36,200
Upstairs.

217
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:40,720
Captain Inoue.

218
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:42,480
Chairman Tang,

219
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,600
can you guarantee

220
00:12:44,600 --> 00:12:46,530
your loyalty to the Imperial Army?

221
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:48,320
Captain Inoue,

222
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,120
I have always been

223
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:51,440
completely loyal to the Imperial Army.

224
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:52,370
That's not true.

225
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:56,000
You've been hiding many things.

226
00:12:56,400 --> 00:12:56,960
No, no,

227
00:12:57,160 --> 00:12:57,760
I haven't.

228
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,720
Absolutely not!

229
00:13:09,040 --> 00:13:09,880
Recently,

230
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,860
we've received some reports.

231
00:13:12,520 --> 00:13:14,120
In Shangbiao Village,

232
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,800
Tanjiawan Village,

233
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,680
and many other households,

234
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:19,240
there are hidden rooms.

235
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,360
Why haven't you

236
00:13:23,280 --> 00:13:26,680
reported this to us?

237
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,160
Captain Inoue,

238
00:13:29,520 --> 00:13:31,280
it's like this.

239
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,920
Not every household on this island

240
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,240
has a hidden room.

241
00:13:35,720 --> 00:13:37,920
Poor families don't have hidden rooms.

242
00:13:39,640 --> 00:13:40,480
Come up.

243
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:56,840
Captain Inoue.

244
00:13:58,280 --> 00:13:59,440
You don't know,

245
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:02,800
this area used to have pirates.

246
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,570
The wealthy families on the island

247
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,480
when building their houses,

248
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,840
constructed secret rooms.

249
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:10,280
When pirates came,

250
00:14:10,680 --> 00:14:12,280
they hid their valuables,

251
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,280
family members and food.

252
00:14:14,720 --> 00:14:15,520
I understand.

253
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:17,080
So,

254
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,060
does the Tan family in the east village have one?

255
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,560
The one we met at the ancestral hall last time,

256
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:24,220
does the Chen family have one?

257
00:14:24,560 --> 00:14:26,000
What about Mr. Ye? Does the Ye family have one too?

258
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:26,760
Yes, they do.

259
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:36,800
Then tell me,

260
00:14:37,440 --> 00:14:40,360
these secret rooms of wealthy families,

261
00:14:40,560 --> 00:14:42,220
where are they usually built?

262
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:44,320
I really don't know that.

263
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:48,160
I've heard some are built in attics,

264
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:50,040
while others are underground.

265
00:14:50,400 --> 00:14:51,840
Secret rooms...

266
00:14:52,040 --> 00:14:54,720
they must all be in hidden places.

267
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,360
Of course.

268
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:59,250
Does anyone on the island know about them?

269
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,800
No.

270
00:15:01,760 --> 00:15:03,160
These wealthy families,

271
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,600
when building their secret rooms,

272
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:06,730
hired people from outside the island.

273
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,730
Island locals can't find them.

274
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,840
You know

275
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,920
the consequences of lying to me?

276
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:18,560
No,

277
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,280
I absolutely wouldn't dare.

278
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:23,120
Everything I've said is true.

279
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:26,000
Alright.

280
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:28,880
Today,

281
00:15:29,120 --> 00:15:30,360
I called you here

282
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:33,320
because there's a very important matter

283
00:15:33,640 --> 00:15:36,440
that your maintenance committee needs to handle.

284
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,280
A few days ago

285
00:15:40,280 --> 00:15:42,800
we shot down an American aircraft.

286
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:46,640
There's still one person from the plane who hasn't been found.

287
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:48,600
Your maintenance committee should notify

288
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,200
all villagers on the island.

289
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:53,220
Anyone who provides information

290
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,440
will be rewarded by our Special Police Unit

291
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:58,680
with 50 jin of rice

